history.content:
<md>cs 161 is pretty chill as a class, wouldn't worry about the workload or anything here.

cs189 is a bit of a mystery. Not sure how listgarten and malik will teach it, but since you have taken 188, 126, and 127, you are probably aptly prepared for the class.

phys 137a: This really depends on your physics background. Personally speaking, I don't think that the 7 series prepares people well for the theoretical sides of upper division physics, the 5 series is much better at that specifically. Not sure if you are a physics person, but if you are it should be fine. 

Overall manageable if you aren't looking to add another techs (maybe a breadth if you really want)</md>

Is this course load manageable? (I've taken CS188, EECS126, EECS127 and Physics 7A and 7B before)
Any recommendations to prepare for these classes? Thanks!
history.subject: 161 + 189 + Physics 137A
